OL,3,CDecision not to charge Bloody Sunday
OL,4,Csoldiers for perjury upheld
OL,6,FIn April 2024, the PPS made the
OL,7,Fdecision not to prosecute 16
OL,8,Findividuals over due to "insufficient
OL,9,Fadmissible evidence" to provide a
OL,10,Freasonable prospect of conviction.
OL,12,FEight of the Bloody Sunday families
OL,13,Fhad asked the PPS to review the
OL,14,Fdecision over perjury charges.
OL,16,FHaving met with relatives of the
OL,17,Fvictims, the PPS confirmed in
OL,18,Fstatement on Wednesday morning that
OL,19,Fthe decision had been upheld.
